WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:10.824 align:middle line:90%


00:00:10.824 --> 00:00:15.400 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, badass is the number
one word that people say to me,

00:00:15.400 --> 00:00:17.100 align:middle line:90%
you know, oh, that's badass.

00:00:17.100 --> 00:00:18.210 align:middle line:90%
Man, you're a badass, man.

00:00:18.210 --> 00:00:19.030 align:middle line:90%
That's badass.

00:00:19.030 --> 00:00:21.560 align:middle line:90%
It's like, all right, badass.

00:00:21.560 --> 00:00:24.470 align:middle line:84%
I'm not really sure
what a badass is.

00:00:24.470 --> 00:00:27.335 align:middle line:84%
I think they mean
willing to endure, like,

00:00:27.335 --> 00:00:29.560 align:middle line:84%
tough as nails kind of
thing, but instead it

00:00:29.560 --> 00:00:30.570 align:middle line:90%
comes out as badass.

00:00:30.570 --> 00:00:32.100 align:middle line:90%
It's like, whatever.

00:00:32.100 --> 00:00:33.280 align:middle line:10%
I'm badass, OK.

00:00:33.280 --> 00:00:42.480 align:middle line:90%


00:00:42.480 --> 00:00:46.290 align:middle line:84%
When they gave me my doctorate,
I still didn't have my speech

00:00:46.290 --> 00:00:48.560 align:middle line:84%
but it was time for me
to get up and make it.

00:00:48.560 --> 00:00:52.010 align:middle line:84%
So I started with the
song because if you

00:00:52.010 --> 00:00:55.315 align:middle line:84%
start with a prayer, then all
the right things will follow.

00:00:55.315 --> 00:01:00.900 align:middle line:90%
[COOL MUSIC]

00:01:00.900 --> 00:01:03.580 align:middle line:90%
So

00:01:03.580 --> 00:01:08.010 align:middle line:90%
[SINGING IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

00:01:08.010 --> 00:01:41.210 align:middle line:90%


00:01:41.210 --> 00:01:44.000 align:middle line:84%
But there's nothing I love
more than my homelands, which

00:01:44.000 --> 00:01:44.875 align:middle line:90%
I live far from.

00:01:44.875 --> 00:01:52.050 align:middle line:90%


00:01:52.050 --> 00:01:57.240 align:middle line:84%
I was in the hills and I
saw a coyote just wandering.

00:01:57.240 --> 00:01:59.020 align:middle line:90%
And it looked so forlorn.

00:01:59.020 --> 00:02:00.840 align:middle line:84%
And it felt like me
and my homelands,

00:02:00.840 --> 00:02:03.600 align:middle line:84%
searching for my tribe,
searching for my people

00:02:03.600 --> 00:02:07.010 align:middle line:90%
and it just seemed so sad.

00:02:07.010 --> 00:02:09.669 align:middle line:84%
So when I think about
that and I sing that song,

00:02:09.669 --> 00:02:13.260 align:middle line:84%
I can feel the wind in
Southern California.

00:02:13.260 --> 00:02:15.750 align:middle line:84%
The Santa Ana's come in and
it's like someone's turned

00:02:15.750 --> 00:02:17.490 align:middle line:90%
on a heater with a large fan.

00:02:17.490 --> 00:02:19.080 align:middle line:10%
And you're standing
in the middle

00:02:19.080 --> 00:02:22.770 align:middle line:10%
of all of your sacred plants,
all of the medicine plants

00:02:22.770 --> 00:02:28.580 align:middle line:10%
and the food plants, and
the world just walks by you

00:02:28.580 --> 00:02:31.350 align:middle line:10%
and they don't take notice.

00:02:31.350 --> 00:02:34.560 align:middle line:84%
By the world I mean the
ants, the deer, the skunks,

00:02:34.560 --> 00:02:36.470 align:middle line:90%
the coyotes.

00:02:36.470 --> 00:02:37.950 align:middle line:90%
They don't take notice.

00:02:37.950 --> 00:02:42.170 align:middle line:84%
They just-- you're
just part of the scene.

00:02:42.170 --> 00:02:44.700 align:middle line:10%
So it just makes me
feel like I'm home.

00:02:44.700 --> 00:03:03.500 align:middle line:90%


00:03:03.500 --> 00:03:05.210 align:middle line:90%
I was talking to an elder.

00:03:05.210 --> 00:03:10.700 align:middle line:84%
And we were talking
about people and what

00:03:10.700 --> 00:03:13.520 align:middle line:84%
they know about their own
selves and cultures and all.

00:03:13.520 --> 00:03:17.000 align:middle line:90%
And this old man said that--

00:03:17.000 --> 00:03:20.755 align:middle line:84%
he said that people today
are like detached seaweed.

00:03:20.755 --> 00:03:24.380 align:middle line:90%


00:03:24.380 --> 00:03:27.500 align:middle line:84%
And, I mean, I think I was told
this like 60 something years

00:03:27.500 --> 00:03:30.470 align:middle line:84%
ago, and it's still
every day in my head

00:03:30.470 --> 00:03:35.005 align:middle line:84%
that I don't want it
to be detached seaweed

00:03:35.005 --> 00:03:37.555 align:middle line:84%
and I don't want others
to be detached seaweed.

00:03:37.555 --> 00:03:42.850 align:middle line:90%


00:03:42.850 --> 00:03:46.460 align:middle line:84%
I'd say the majority of
people are lost because you're

00:03:46.460 --> 00:03:50.080 align:middle line:90%
supposed to be an independent.

00:03:50.080 --> 00:03:52.460 align:middle line:84%
Just the thought of it,
they, go West, young man,

00:03:52.460 --> 00:03:53.480 align:middle line:90%
and do good things.

00:03:53.480 --> 00:03:55.990 align:middle line:84%
And it's all about the
individual succeeding.

00:03:55.990 --> 00:04:04.300 align:middle line:10%
And then the idea of success,
that makes people lonely,

00:04:04.300 --> 00:04:06.435 align:middle line:10%
but it just separates us.

00:04:06.435 --> 00:04:11.010 align:middle line:90%


00:04:11.010 --> 00:04:13.290 align:middle line:84%
And, of course, they
never fill that thing

00:04:13.290 --> 00:04:15.840 align:middle line:84%
that you need which is really
community and one another

00:04:15.840 --> 00:04:19.060 align:middle line:84%
and relationships and a
relationship with the planet,

00:04:19.060 --> 00:04:22.115 align:middle line:84%
relationship with space,
relationship with all things.

00:04:22.115 --> 00:04:26.590 align:middle line:90%


00:04:26.590 --> 00:04:28.710 align:middle line:10%
What makes us lost is
we've lost each other.

00:04:28.710 --> 00:04:34.170 align:middle line:90%


00:04:34.170 --> 00:04:38.793 align:middle line:84%
We have been dismembered for so
long that it's time to remember.

00:04:38.793 --> 00:04:43.960 align:middle line:90%


00:04:43.960 --> 00:04:46.600 align:middle line:84%
We need to come together
in order for those memories

00:04:46.600 --> 00:04:50.500 align:middle line:84%
that we're looking for because
they're village memories

00:04:50.500 --> 00:04:52.470 align:middle line:84%
and you don't get
them individually.

00:04:52.470 --> 00:04:57.310 align:middle line:84%
We have to remember in order
to put ourselves back together

00:04:57.310 --> 00:04:58.110 align:middle line:90%
again.

00:04:58.110 --> 00:05:12.120 align:middle line:90%


00:05:12.120 --> 00:05:14.133 align:middle line:84%
And this was put
on by Keone Nunes.

00:05:14.133 --> 00:05:15.300 align:middle line:90%
And it goes all the way to--

00:05:15.300 --> 00:05:17.190 align:middle line:84%
I'm trying to see
where-- about here.

00:05:17.190 --> 00:05:20.190 align:middle line:84%
And in Hawaii and
it's called makapuu.

00:05:20.190 --> 00:05:26.280 align:middle line:84%
And the word literally
means blind, but it means--

00:05:26.280 --> 00:05:28.970 align:middle line:84%
spiritually it means one who
can see what others cannot.

00:05:28.970 --> 00:05:35.340 align:middle line:90%


00:05:35.340 --> 00:05:38.530 align:middle line:84%
I think what I see in other
people is this bright and shiny,

00:05:38.530 --> 00:05:40.650 align:middle line:90%
unadulterated light.

00:05:40.650 --> 00:05:43.530 align:middle line:84%
And that's where all my
friends and family go,

00:05:43.530 --> 00:05:44.740 align:middle line:90%
you need some filters.

00:05:44.740 --> 00:05:46.470 align:middle line:90%
It's not all light.

00:05:46.470 --> 00:05:48.910 align:middle line:90%
But that's what I see.

00:05:48.910 --> 00:05:52.265 align:middle line:84%
Even in people I really don't
like I still see that light.

00:05:52.265 --> 00:05:57.990 align:middle line:90%


00:05:57.990 --> 00:06:00.880 align:middle line:90%
Some people can only see ugly.

00:06:00.880 --> 00:06:05.830 align:middle line:84%
And maybe because I've looked
through an eye hole in my camera

00:06:05.830 --> 00:06:10.360 align:middle line:84%
since I was eight and 1/2,
nine years old but I just see

00:06:10.360 --> 00:06:13.180 align:middle line:84%
everything as
beautiful, everything.

00:06:13.180 --> 00:06:16.090 align:middle line:90%
If it's got the right lighting.

00:06:16.090 --> 00:06:17.052 align:middle line:90%
Everything's beautiful.

00:06:17.052 --> 00:06:18.260 align:middle line:90%
People are beautiful, plants.

00:06:18.260 --> 00:06:19.490 align:middle line:90%
Everything is beautiful.

00:06:19.490 --> 00:06:20.810 align:middle line:90%
Death is beautiful.

00:06:20.810 --> 00:06:22.376 align:middle line:90%
Life is beautiful.

00:06:22.376 --> 00:06:28.510 align:middle line:90%


00:06:28.510 --> 00:06:32.030 align:middle line:84%
Beauty is always right there
sitting right next to ugly,

00:06:32.030 --> 00:06:35.240 align:middle line:84%
and that's what
I've always seen.

00:06:35.240 --> 00:06:36.690 align:middle line:90%
That's what I love about people.

00:06:36.690 --> 00:06:43.790 align:middle line:90%


00:06:43.790 --> 00:06:46.730 align:middle line:10%
Like many, many natives
in the Americas,

00:06:46.730 --> 00:06:48.790 align:middle line:10%
we consider ourselves
star people.

00:06:48.790 --> 00:06:51.520 align:middle line:90%


00:06:51.520 --> 00:06:56.690 align:middle line:84%
In my opinion, our journey
is the star journey.

00:06:56.690 --> 00:06:57.820 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, all of it.

00:06:57.820 --> 00:07:05.175 align:middle line:90%


00:07:05.175 --> 00:07:07.050 align:middle line:84%
The thing that I hold
on to with the sciences

00:07:07.050 --> 00:07:09.210 align:middle line:84%
is that they say
that we are comprised

00:07:09.210 --> 00:07:12.660 align:middle line:84%
of some 90 some
percent of stardust

00:07:12.660 --> 00:07:14.940 align:middle line:84%
or we're comprised of the
same things that comprise--

00:07:14.940 --> 00:07:18.360 align:middle line:90%
that are found in space.

00:07:18.360 --> 00:07:24.610 align:middle line:84%
We are basically spaced little
water bags, flesh water bags

00:07:24.610 --> 00:07:27.180 align:middle line:84%
but the stuff that
we are made of,

00:07:27.180 --> 00:07:30.790 align:middle line:84%
you can go out and find
it anywhere in space.

00:07:30.790 --> 00:07:32.720 align:middle line:90%
So how can we be disconnected?

00:07:32.720 --> 00:07:36.900 align:middle line:84%
How can we not be a part
if we're comprised of this?

00:07:36.900 --> 00:07:38.655 align:middle line:84%
It's a lot of
ignoring of reality.

00:07:38.655 --> 00:08:03.542 align:middle line:90%


00:08:03.542 --> 00:08:21.110 align:middle line:90%
[SINGING IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

00:08:21.110 --> 00:08:24.540 align:middle line:84%
I do believe that
we're all one family.

00:08:24.540 --> 00:08:27.420 align:middle line:84%
The Cosmic Serpent Conference
scientist he kept saying,

00:08:27.420 --> 00:08:29.220 align:middle line:84%
you Indigenous
people hurt my head.

00:08:29.220 --> 00:08:31.810 align:middle line:84%
So I asked him, I said, well,
what planet are you from?

00:08:31.810 --> 00:08:32.669 align:middle line:90%
He said, Earth.

00:08:32.669 --> 00:08:34.470 align:middle line:10%
I said, well, so
am I. Doesn't that

00:08:34.470 --> 00:08:36.929 align:middle line:10%
make us both
indigenous to Earth?

00:08:36.929 --> 00:08:38.460 align:middle line:90%
And he said, well, yeah.

00:08:38.460 --> 00:08:41.919 align:middle line:84%
And I said, well, we
have our differences

00:08:41.919 --> 00:08:43.919 align:middle line:90%
but we are all the same people.

00:08:43.919 --> 00:08:48.430 align:middle line:84%
Now, I don't want to
have your religion,

00:08:48.430 --> 00:08:51.450 align:middle line:84%
you don't want to have
mine and that's not

00:08:51.450 --> 00:08:53.680 align:middle line:90%
what all being one is to me.

00:08:53.680 --> 00:08:58.890 align:middle line:84%
Being one is that
underneath we are all one.

00:08:58.890 --> 00:09:01.890 align:middle line:84%
My child hurts his
foot, the child

00:09:01.890 --> 00:09:04.120 align:middle line:90%
cries, I cry, we fix it up.

00:09:04.120 --> 00:09:06.760 align:middle line:84%
And if that happens on the
other side of the planet,

00:09:06.760 --> 00:09:10.180 align:middle line:84%
I don't think that anyone is
going to act any differently.

00:09:10.180 --> 00:09:12.720 align:middle line:84%
They are going to
care for that child.

00:09:12.720 --> 00:09:15.570 align:middle line:90%
How is that not being the same?

00:09:15.570 --> 00:09:20.020 align:middle line:84%
It's not like we act bizarrely
in the same instances.

00:09:20.020 --> 00:09:21.215 align:middle line:90%
We act exactly the same.

00:09:21.215 --> 00:09:31.470 align:middle line:90%


00:09:31.470 --> 00:09:33.310 align:middle line:84%
I don't have to
dance your dance,

00:09:33.310 --> 00:09:35.550 align:middle line:84%
I don't have to sing
your song in order

00:09:35.550 --> 00:09:38.090 align:middle line:90%
to be you and be a part.

00:09:38.090 --> 00:09:43.740 align:middle line:90%


00:09:43.740 --> 00:09:46.250 align:middle line:84%
Everybody's needed
in that web of life.

00:09:46.250 --> 00:09:49.810 align:middle line:90%


00:09:49.810 --> 00:09:52.630 align:middle line:84%
If we look at the path,
we do not see the sky.

00:09:52.630 --> 00:09:56.680 align:middle line:84%
We are Earth people on a
spiritual journey to the stars.

00:09:56.680 --> 00:10:00.100 align:middle line:84%
Our Earth walk is to look
within, to know who we are,

00:10:00.100 --> 00:10:03.855 align:middle line:84%
to see that we are
connected to all things.

00:10:03.855 --> 00:10:08.050 align:middle line:84%
That there is no separation,
only in the mind.

00:10:08.050 --> 00:10:26.000 align:middle line:90%